&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;11&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559684&amp;quot;:-2,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Lead, mentor, and motivate engineers to achieve individual and team goals while fostering a collaborative, high-accountability environment&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;11&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559684&amp;quot;:-2,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777815&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;hybridMultilevel&amp;quot;}&quot; data-aria-posinset=&quot;1&quot; data-aria-level=&quot;1&quot;&gt;Own technical direction and day-to-day engineering execution for GovIntel and GovChannel workstreams &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-leveltext=&quot;&quot; data-font=&quot;Symbol&quot; data-listid=&quot;11&quot; data-list-defn-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;335552541&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559684&amp;quot;:-2,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559991&amp;quot;:360,&amp;quot;469769226&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Symbol&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469769242&amp;quot;:[8226],&amp;quot;469777803&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;left&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;469777804&amp;quot;:&amp;quo

&lt;p&gt;Shape the future of AI-powered growth for the Architecture, Engineering &amp;amp; Construction (AEC) industries! We’re looking for a Product Manager who thrives at the intersection of customer insight, product strategy, and AI-driven execution to help define and launch the next generation of capabilities on Unanet’s AI-first platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a “builder” role, not a traditional backlog management position. Partnering closely with Product, UX, Engineering, and Go-to-Market teams, you will own the journey from problem framing to product delivery, translating customer needs into clear product intent and rapidly turning ideas into market-ready solutions. Success will be measured by outcomes: accelerating customer growth, driving user adoption, and creating differentiated value that strengthens Unanet’s long-term leadership in the AEC market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and drive a forward-looking roadmap for AI-first AEC capabilities for Unanet’s GrowthStudio product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead product discovery, framing, and prioritization for customer-facing AI-enabled workflows and experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage internal AI tooling across the full product lifecycle, from discovery and strategy through prototyping, PRD creation, and refinement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with UX and Engineering to shape agentic workflows; move quickly from concept to validated prototype, and ensure we are solving the right problems for our customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics, evaluation approaches, and feedback loops for LLM- and agent-driven experiences, including human-in-the-loop validation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate strategy and research into actionable requirements and release plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively across technical and non-technical stakeholders, including Engineering on requirements and Marketing on Go-to-Market strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track competitive and market developments in AEC and use that insight to inform our roadmap, positioning, and moat-building decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help evolve how Product works in an AI-first organization by modeling strong use of AI in day-to-day product management practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in the Architecture, Engineering, and Construction (AEC) industry, or deep experience building software products for AEC customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience translating customer and market insights into product requirements, prototypes, and launched software capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working in an Agile or AI-accelerated product development environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI-powered products, including LLMs, agentic workflows, AI-assisted experiences, or adjacent technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, with the ability to define problems, evaluate data, identify risks, and make informed product decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate effectively across Product, Engineering, UX, Marketing, and customer-facing teams, communicating complex concepts to technical and non-technical audiences alike&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with technical architecture, data models, information retrieval systems, and product evaluation frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication, presentation, and stakeholder management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with responsible AI principles, including fairness, transparency, and accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-directed, collaborative, and execution-oriented, with a track record of delivering high-quality solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness and ability to travel to customer and non-customer sites (~15%)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Differentiators &lt;/strong&

&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Operations Associate to help strengthen how Unanet’s Product organization plans, executes, learns, and improves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will support the operating system of Product by bringing structure to ambiguity, improving team rhythms and workflows, maintaining strong documentation and reporting, and helping cross-functional teams move from ideas to action with greater clarity, consistency, and speed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner closely with Product Management, UX, Engineering, and customer-facing teams to support planning, alignment, decision-making, and continuous improvement across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a highly organized, analytically minded, adaptable professional who enjoys building better ways of working, thrives in evolving environments, and actively uses AI-enabled tools to improve quality, speed, and execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product planning and operating processes, including roadmap reviews, intake workflows, dependency tracking, release coordination, and follow-up on key initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve team processes, templates, standards, and documentation to promote consistency, visibility, and execution quality across the product organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Management, Engineering, Design, customer-facing teams, and other stakeholders to support alignment, decision-making, and effective execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and maintain dashboards, reports, and analysis that provide visibility into delivery progress, product health, adoption signals, and operational performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate product documentation, decision logs, and internal knowledge resources so teams can move faster with stronger shared context&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify manual, repetitive, or unclear workflows and recommend improvements through process refinement, standardization, automation, and AI-enabled tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools responsibly to support research, synthesis, drafting, analysis, knowledge retrieval, and workflow acceleration while validating outputs with sound judgment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help identify, test, and scale practical AI use cases that improve how Product works, including meeting summarization, content drafting, workflow support, knowledge access, and lightweight automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to an iterative operating model where processes evolve as the team learns, priorities shift, and new tools create better ways of working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help evolve how Product works in an AI-first organization by modeling curiosity, adaptability, and strong day-to-day use of AI in support of quality and speed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your First 90 Days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your First 30 Days, you’ll build a strong understanding of the Product organization’s operating rhythms, planning processes, documentation standards, tooling, and cross-functional stakeholder landscape. You’ll learn how roadmap reviews, intake, release coordination, reporting, and knowledge management work today while identifying opportunities to improve clarity, consistency, and follow-through.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In your First 60 Days, you’ll begin taking ownership of core operating workflows and recurring processes, helping improve documentation, dashboards, reporting, and coordination across teams. You’ll support stronger visibility into product health and delivery progress while partnering with stakeholders to refine team processes and reduce friction in day-to-day execution.&lt;/p&gt;
